Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.60,1:25:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,she's had her way ever since.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.71,1:25:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All information no matter how seemingly\Nuh correct is always presumptive. So
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.40,1:25:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,wisdom part of spiritual evolution\Nuh is the development progressive
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.04,1:25:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,development of wisdom.\NOne thing that is important to learn is
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.36,1:25:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that all information and all knowledge\Nand everything you think and believe is
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.44,1:25:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,presumptive only\Nand that it may it's subject to change
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.23,1:25:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,later. Everything you know, think or\Nbelieve is provisional.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.92,1:25:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is provisional. It's\Npresumptive and provisional. So with
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.28,1:26:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,wisdom, you learn to hold back a certain\Ndegree
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.28,1:26:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and\Nmore will be added later. Expect that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.63,1:26:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,more will be added. Look, all the years\Nsince World War II and many of the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.28,1:26:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,things that happened in World War II\Nthat were extremely critical are only
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.44,1:26:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,coming to light now, 50 some odd years\Nlater. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.92,1:26:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact the Japanese had almost\Nperfected an atomic bomb wasn't even
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.36,1:26:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,known until the papers of some\NJapanese physicists were made public in
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.71,1:26:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the mid70s.\NAmerican public didn't know it. Nobody
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.56,1:26:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,even knew it. They were just a couple of\Nmonths away from atomic bomb themsself
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.23,1:26:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway. So that was on History Channel\Nor something like that. So even though
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.52,1:26:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it seems like all has been known, there\Nis yet more to know. So we we then have
Dialogue: 0,1:26:54.00,1:26:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain modesty about anything we\Nthink or believe because we know that
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.80,1:27:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,more may be added and the whole picture\Nmay be changed. All you need is one more
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.76,1:27:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,piece of information and the whole chess\Nboard changes. You move the bishop from
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.08,1:27:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,one square to this square, the whole\Ngame just totally changed. moving one
Dialogue: 0,1:27:13.04,1:27:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,little piece of information.\NAll information is presumptive.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.04,1:27:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We already covered Yev by college\Nand we covered Protagoras's dictim that
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.67,1:27:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,reality is purely subject subjective\Npresumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.63,1:27:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That is also a basic tenant of\Nrelativism
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.40,1:27:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that all information etc is only a point\Nof view. Yeah. And there is no such
Dialogue: 0,1:27:39.92,1:27:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,thing as the absolute.\NNo such thing as the absolute. And uh
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.76,1:27:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,once in a while I get an indignant\Nletter. Somebody gets very indignant
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.96,1:27:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when I I speak about the absolute\Nbecause to relativism there is no such
