Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.44,1:29:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are really different different\Nparadigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.12,1:29:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with atheism and\Nskepticism and all such things is that
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.08,1:29:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear domain of causality uh the\N400s
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.36,1:29:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,uh the linear is one domain and the\Nnonlinear is another domain and the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.40,1:30:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,limited mind cannot grasp that there is\Na domain and a context
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.32,1:30:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,of context that is greater than the\Npedestrian mundane in world of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.80,1:30:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,See, so it cannot comprehend that\Nthere's any reality greater than itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.67,1:30:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll notice skepticism, which\Ncalibrates very low, by the way, because
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.15,1:30:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a form of nihilism.\NSkepticism calibrates very low. And it
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.28,1:30:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,does so because it thinks the only\Nreality is content and linear causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.15,1:30:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't realize that there's\Nanything that exists beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.92,1:30:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness the level of the 400s.\NIt thinks that you know if you can't
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.92,1:30:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,prove it etc. So it poo poos religion\Nand faith and all these things. But as
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.23,1:30:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we mentioned before the one thing that\Nskepticism has tremendous faith in is
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.00,1:31:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,its own self.\NThe skeptic re ridicules faith but it
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.56,1:31:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,has profound faith in its own\Nconvictions and its own skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.71,1:31:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So that that is the paradox really\Nprotagonist's paradox is the when the
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.44,1:31:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth absolute truth is unknowable\Nand the skeptic is uh definitely
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.32,1:31:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,has faith in the truth of that statement\Nthat the absolute truth is unknowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.04,1:31:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's unknowable, then what the\Nskeptic is saying has no basis in
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.52,1:31:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,reality whatsoever. Huh?\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.15,1:31:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What?\NWe down to the last page. I want to make
